-> Fancy
    Hephaestus: Mmm, this meal is delightful; the flavors are wonderfully subtle.
    Hephaestus: I think you are right Aelius; I shouldn't fight Ares, I think I should talk to him.
    Aelius: Huh, that’s actually really mature-
    Hephaestus: And when I show him the depths of my passion, I can surely convince him to cede the field, leaving me free to pursue Aphrodite once more.
    Aelius: Hephaestus, I'm not sure you should-
    Hephaestus: Hush! These matters of the heart can wait no longer!
    Hephaestus: I must show that braggart that I am not afraid!
    Aelius: Hephaestus...
    Hephaestus: I must be off, Aelius.
-> Playful
    Hephaestus: Mmm, this is delightful!
    Hephaestus: Okay, I'll tell you what – you may be right about confronting Ares.
    Hephaestus: However, I think I know how to knock that smile off his face regardless.
    Aelius: Oh no.
    Hephaestus: I should go over his head and talk to Aphrodite directly!
    Aelius: Huh, that's actually really mature-
    Hephaestus: And I shall win back her heart with the most romantic token she has ever seen.
    Hephaestus: Bronzework so grand it shall sweep her off her feet!
    Aelius: I suppose it's better than nothing.
    Hephaestus: Hush! The romance swelling in my chest cannot be quenched.
    Hephaestus: I must be off to begin my work!
-> Spicy
    Hephaestus: Mmm, this dish has a bite to it. It's very hot.
    Hephaestus: Well, thank you for the meal, Aelius.
    Hephaestus: I shall be well fortified for my confrontation with Ares.

    Aelius: I really don’t think-

    Hephaestus: Hush! These matterss of the heart can wait no longer!
    Hephaestus: I must show that braggart that I am not afraid, that I am willing to fight for Aphrodite.

    Aelius: Hephaestus...
    Hephaestus: I must be off, Aelius.

